{"id": "25890385", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=25890385", "title": "The Centre for Polish Studies", "text": "The Centre for Polish Studies\n\nThe Centre for Polish Studies (Centrum Kształcenia Języka Polskiego in Polish) is a Warsaw-based school of Polish language. The school organizes courses in Warsaw, Sopot and Cracow. It is a private institution established in 2000 by Anna Jurewicz-Sawa, a teacher of Polish as a foreign language.\n\nThe Centre for Polish Studies promotes itself as a school with a mission of popularizing Polish culture and language among foreigners. Their website reads: “Our mission is to help foreigners get to know not only Polish, but also Poland: we believe that language, although it is key to understanding a country and its people, is not enough – therefore, we also teach our students culture, economy and history of Poland”.\n"}
{"id": "50533797", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki?curid=50533797", "title": "Îlot Pasteur", "text": "Îlot Pasteur\n\nThe Îlot Pasteur is a building on the western edge of Monaco under construction since 2016. It will be home to a new middle school, a post office, a recycling center, a data center, an underground carpark, etc.\n\nIts construction was announced in 2013, and it began in January 2016. The building is designed by architects Christian Curau and François Lallemand.\n\n"}
